               <p>The prisoner, in his defence, did not deny the charge, but said</p>
               <p>"that Hayward had</p>
               <p>"many times endeavoured to persuade him to</p>
               <p>"rob his master, but he had always refused to</p>
               <p>"to do, but that Hayward came to him that</p>
               <p>"Sunday, and would oblige him to submit to</p>
               <p>"the robbery, notwithstanding he remonstrated</p>
               <p>"very strongly with Hayward to the contrary."</p>
